fields.description:
The DNS TCP handler currently checks the message size and logs an error for messages larger than 1024 bytes:

{code}
			if(inputLength > DNSProperties.MAX_MESSAGE_SIZE) {
				LOG.error("Maximum message size exceeded. Ignoring request.");
			}
			byte[] inBytes = new byte[inputLength];
{code}

The error says the message is ignored, but these "large" messages are processed. The length value is an unsigned short so the maximum possible value is 65535.

comments.body:
[~mmunn1] It appears that somebody already changed the code:
  if( inputLength > DNSProperties.MAX_MESSAGE_SIZE ) {
            throw new IOException("Maximum message size exceeded. Ignoring request.");
          }

I think that exception may cause a problem if people queries with over 1k data. I'd simply remove the check entirely or raise the MAX_SIZE [~sjones] [~decker] .
